---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const lastUpdated = (await getCollection('framework'))
	.map(a => a.data.date)
	.filter(Boolean)
	.sort()
	.at(-1);
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			main {
				max-width: 720px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 3rem 1.25rem 5rem;
			}
			.page-title {
				font-family: "Playfair Display", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
				font-weight: 700;
				line-height: 1.2;
				margin: 0 0 1.75rem 0;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.opening {
				font-family: "Inter", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: 1.08rem;
				line-height: 1.95;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			.opening p {
				margin-bottom: 1.6em;
			}
			.opening p:last-of-type {
				margin-bottom: 0;
			}
			.opening strong {
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.cta-row {
				margin-top: 3rem;
				padding-top: 2.5rem;
				border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
				text-align: center;
			}
			.cta-link {
				display: inline-block;
				font-family: "Inter", Georgia, serif;
				font-size: 0.88rem;
				font-weight: 600;
				letter-spacing: 0.14em;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				color: var(--accent);
				text-decoration: none;
				padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
				border: 1.5px solid var(--accent);
				border-radius: 4px;
				transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
			}
			.cta-link:hover {
				background: var(--accent);
				color: #fff;
			}
			@media (max-width: 600px) {
				main {
					padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
				}
				.opening {
					font-size: 1rem;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1 class="page-title">Navigating faith and family in the age of AI</h1>
			<div class="opening">
				<p>You've felt it. Something in the air has changed — not all at once, but steadily, the way a season turns. The kids ask questions you don't have clean answers for. The work is shifting. The world your parents handed you and the world your children will inherit look less and less like the same place.</p>
				<p>We're ordinary Christian families trying to walk through that honestly. We're not doomsayers and we're not techno-optimists. We believe God made us to use tools, to build, to create — and that the long history of human ingenuity is part of how He works in the world. But we also believe that what is happening now, this rapid, relentless remaking of work and relationships and identity, deserves more than a shrug or a scroll. It deserves our full, prayerful attention.</p>
				<p>This is a place for that attention. The articles here won't give you all the answers, but they may help you see the terrain more clearly, ask better questions, and remind you that you and your family are not wandering alone. Others are out here too, navigating the same unfamiliar ground, holding the same ancient faith.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="cta-row">
				<a class="cta-link" href="/articles">Read the Articles →</a>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer lastUpdated={lastUpdated} />
	</body>
</html>
